Grape Salad, My Family's Recipe
(easily scaled)

(everything listed here is available at costco)

- 1.5lb of grapes, red or green.
- 8oz cream cheese.
- 1 cup white sugar
- 2 cups Greek yogurt, unflavoured

- - preparing the wet part
- pour the greek yogurt in first
- add cream cheese
- add sugar
- mix until it apears homogenous

- - preparing the rest
- pick grapes off vine, discard any mushy ones
- put into mixing bowl, then toss until all grapes are covered.

- goes great as a side, or a snack during work.
